  "market_context": "Daily chart showed a strong down move followed by a reversal candle on Tuesday (Aug 6, 2025) with a long lower wick to 1.14200, retracing into a fair value gap zone (1.14200–1.15200). Analyst waited for continuation setup on Wednesday.",
  "key_observation": "The Tuesday daily candle was a reversal candle with large opposing run (long lower wick), indicating exhaustion of downside; price retraced into a fair value gap, setting up a high-probability long continuation on Wednesday after change in state of delivery on 1H.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the daily reversal candle on Tuesday (Aug 6) with a long lower wick reaching 1.14200 and closing near its open, confirming a reversal after prior expansion down.",
    "Step 2: Noted price retraced into a fair value gap zone (1.14200–1.15200) marked by yellow rectangle, establishing a point of interest for potential long entry.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to 1-hour timeframe to confirm change in state of delivery: identified series of down-close candles and awaited close above them to validate protected swing low.",
    "Step 4: Observed price retested the FVG zone, formed a new swing low, then closed above the series of down-close candles—triggering a long setup on the next candle’s open with stop below the protected low.",
    "Step 5: Took long trade targeting 2R, with price subsequently moving higher to reach the projected target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Long trade executed on Wednesday open after CISD confirmation; price moved higher achieving ~2R target.",
  "lessons": "Reversal candles with large wicks require patience—wait for candle 3 continuation after CISD confirmation. Retracement into a fair value gap provides a high-probability POI for entries aligned with HTF bias.",
